A new Ebola jab is being given to people living in the West African countries most badly hit by the virus after human trials in unaffected countries .
Scientists hope that immunisation is possible with just one injection after ` highly promising results ' in the first 138 healthy adults who were vaccinated with various doses .
The vaccine is based on an animal virus called vesicular virus virus that is combined with a portion of the Ebola virus .
